<subSubSection id="4FFC65060B7F164E78E8F9D8231EF96D" pageId="15" pageNumber="120" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="0759368D0B7F164E78E8F9D8231EF96D" blockId="15.[136,1452,1454,2092]" pageId="15" pageNumber="120">
<emphasis id="3592EA9F0B7F164E78E8F9D826D7F99D" bold="true" box="[189,397,1562,1588]" pageId="15" pageNumber="120">Taxonomic notes:</emphasis>
— 
<taxonomicName id="C0E64D0E0B7F164E79FCF9D82545F99D" authorityName="Krapovickas" authorityYear="2003" box="[425,543,1562,1588]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Malvaceae" genus="Sida" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malvales" pageId="15" pageNumber="120" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="reitzii">
<emphasis id="3592EA9F0B7F164E79FCF9D82545F99D" box="[425,543,1562,1588]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="120">Sida reitzii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be distinguished from other species of section 
<emphasis id="3592EA9F0B7F164E7C1DF9D823BAF99D" box="[1096,1248,1562,1588]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="120">Distichifoliae</emphasis>
by the presence of 8–10 mericarps with longer aristae (
<quantity id="C01E9B680B7F164E7A45F9FC2537F9F0" box="[528,621,1598,1625]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0" metricValueMax="4.0" metricValueMin="2.0" pageId="15" pageNumber="120" unit="mm" value="3.0" valueMax="4.0" valueMin="2.0">2–4 mm</quantity>
long), staminal tube glabrous, abaxial surface of petals with small glandular trichomes, mericarps glabrous or with glandular trichomes, adaxial surface of leaves with simple adpressed trichomes, abaxial surface of leaves subglabrous with small stellate trichomes (
<figureCitation id="9FDD2A080B7F164E7B2AF9442343F909" box="[895,1049,1670,1696]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="16.[136,229,1921,1943]" captionTargetBox="[222,1366,281,1896]" captionTargetId="figure-66@16.[222,1366,281,1896]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURE 7. A–E. Sida potentilloides. A. Flower. Adaxial surface of leaf. C. Abaxial surface of leaf. D. Branch with leaves, immature schizocarps and flower bud. E. Branch with leaves and mature schizocarps. F–J. Sida ramoniana. F. Abaxial surface of leaf indument. G. Calyx basis indument tomentose. H. Stem indument pubescent. I. Margin of leaf dentate-crenate. J–O. Sida reitzii. J. Habit. K. Schizocarps in terminal glomerules. L. Adaxial surface of leaf. M. Abaxial surface of leaf. N. Flower. O. Branch. Photographs A–I by Martin Grings (F–J from K. Hagelund 2228, HAS) and J–O by Luís Funez." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6415503" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6415503/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="120">Figures 7J–O</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="9FDD2A080B7F164E7C71F9442302F909" box="[1060,1112,1670,1696]" captionStart="FIGURE 14" captionStartId="26.[136,229,1957,1979]" captionTargetBox="[196,1391,245,1933]" captionTargetId="figure-54@26.[196,1391,245,1933]" captionTargetPageId="26" captionText="FIGURE 14. Mericarps. A. Sida anomala. B. Sida confusa. C. Sida farroupilhensis. D. Sida glaziovii. E. Sida cerradoensis. F. Sida cordifolia. G. Sida dubia. H. Sida linifolia. I. Sida lonchitis. J. Sida nemorensis. K. Sida paradoxa. L. Sida planicaulis. M. Sida potentilloides.N. Sida reitzii. O. Sida regnellii. P. Sida rhombifolia.Q. Sida riedelii. R. Sida rubifolia.S. Sida spinosa.T. Sida tuberculata. U. Sida urens. V. Sida viarum. Photographs by Martin Grings." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6415519" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6415519/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="120">14N</figureCitation>
; 
<tableCitation id="4A6403360B7F164E7C36F94423E9F909" box="[1123,1203,1670,1696]" captionStart="TABLE 1" captionStartId="2.[136,224,340,364]" captionTargetBox="[144,1440,425,1289]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="TABLE 1. Sections of Sida with species occurring in Rio Grande do Sul state, and their diagnostic features, according to Fryxell (1985) and Krapovickas (2003)." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/539966050B72164378DDFE962568FE39" pageId="15" pageNumber="120" tableUuid="539966050B72164378DDFE962568FE39">Table 1</tableCitation>
) (
<bibRefCitation id="63774B7C0B7F164E7C98F94422FAF909" author="Krapovickas, A." box="[1229,1440,1670,1696]" pageId="15" pageNumber="120" pagination="83 - 121" refId="ref19352" refString="Krapovickas, A. (2003) Sida seccion Distichifolia (Monteiro) Krapov. comb. nov., stat. nov. (Malvaceae-Malveae). Bonplandia 12: 83 - 121. https: // doi. org / 10.30972 / bon. 121 - 41407" type="journal article" year="2003">Krapovickas 2003</bibRefCitation>
). In the present work, photos of the species in its habitat are presented for the first time
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="4FFC65060B7F164E78E8F90C255EF834" pageId="15" pageNumber="120" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="0759368D0B7F164E78E8F90C255EF834" blockId="15.[136,1452,1454,2092]" pageId="15" pageNumber="120">
<emphasis id="3592EA9F0B7F164E78E8F90C25B9F941" bold="true" box="[189,739,1742,1768]" pageId="15" pageNumber="120">Distribution, habitat and conservation status:</emphasis>
—According to 
<bibRefCitation id="63774B7C0B7F164E7BC9F90C2327F941" author="Krapovickas, A." box="[924,1149,1742,1768]" pageId="15" pageNumber="120" pagination="83 - 121" refId="ref19352" refString="Krapovickas, A. (2003) Sida seccion Distichifolia (Monteiro) Krapov. comb. nov., stat. nov. (Malvaceae-Malveae). Bonplandia 12: 83 - 121. https: // doi. org / 10.30972 / bon. 121 - 41407" type="journal article" year="2003">Krapovickas (2003)</bibRefCitation>
the species occurs only in state of 
<collectingRegion id="C522F86F0B7F164E78B1F93026D6F8A5" box="[228,396,1778,1804]" country="Brazil" name="Santa Catarina" pageId="15" pageNumber="120">Santa Catarina</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry id="7FF1761D0B7F164E79CCF93026BBF8A5" box="[409,481,1778,1804]" name="Brazil" pageId="15" pageNumber="120">Brazil</collectingCountry>
. 
<bibRefCitation id="63774B7C0B7F164E79B8F93025D6F8A5" author="Bovini, M. G." box="[493,652,1778,1804]" pageId="15" pageNumber="120" refId="ref18092" refString="Bovini, M. G. (2020) Sida in Lista de Especies da Flora do Brasil. Jardim Botanico do Rio de Janeiro. Available from: http: // floradobrasil. jbrj. gov. br / jabot / floradobrasil / FB 9206 (accessed 7 July 2020)" type="url" year="2020">Bovini (2020)</bibRefCitation>
also mentioned the species to the state of 
<collectingRegion id="C522F86F0B7F164E7C27F9302240F8A5" box="[1138,1306,1778,1804]" country="Brazil" name="Rio de Janeiro" pageId="15" pageNumber="120">Rio de Janeiro</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry id="7FF1761D0B7F164E7D73F9302234F8A5" box="[1318,1390,1778,1804]" name="Brazil" pageId="15" pageNumber="120">Brazil</collectingCountry>
. This work presents the first record of the species for the state of 
<collectingRegion id="C522F86F0B7F164E7B5BF8D42484F899" box="[782,990,1814,1840]" country="Brazil" name="Rio Grande do Sul" pageId="15" pageNumber="120">Rio Grande do Sul</collectingRegion>
, where it occurs in Tropical forest (
<figureCitation id="9FDD2A080B7F164E7D35F8D427CDF8FD" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="17.[136,229,1953,1975]" captionTargetBox="[267,1344,252,1880]" captionTargetId="figure-17@17.[205,1383,190,1929]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURE 8. Distribution map of Sida riedelii, S. ramoniana, S. regnellii, S. reitzii and S. tuberculata in Rio Grande do Sul state, Brazil." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6415505" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6415505/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="120">Figure 8</figureCitation>
), in edges or understory of Forests. With the available records, the species is here considered Least Concern (LC) with an EOO of 
<quantity id="C01E9B680B7F164E7913F89C26B5F8D2" box="[326,495,1886,1915]" metricMagnitude="7" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.7118693" pageId="15" pageNumber="120" unit="km" value="87118.693">87,118.693 km</quantity>
² and an AOO of 
<quantity id="C01E9B680B7F164E7AE0F89C245BF8D2" box="[693,769,1886,1915]" metricMagnitude="4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.6" pageId="15" pageNumber="120" unit="km" value="56.0">56 km</quantity>
². Although it can be considered EN by the AOO, conditions B(a), B(b) and B(c) were not met.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
